Here are the authoritative public test cases for feature3_callback_parse:
{
  "description": "Parse a redirect/callback query string (the part after the separator) into a structured result. Each key/value pair is URL-decoded. The token-lifetime field, when present, is converted to an integer; when absent it is reported as a null lifetime. Both successful authorization results and provider error responses are parsed the same way.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "op": "parse_query",
